Package com.googlecode.cqengine.metadata

Class SortedAttributeMetadata<A extends Comparable<A>,​O>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.googlecode.cqengine.metadata.AttributeMetadata<A,​O>
      • com.googlecode.cqengine.metadata.SortedAttributeMetadata<A,​O>
  • public class SortedAttributeMetadata<A extends Comparable<A>,​O>
extends AttributeMetadata<A,​O>
    Provides access to metadata in sorted order for a given attribute. Allows attribute values to be traversed in ascending or descending order, and supports range queries. See MetadataEngine for more details.

    This requires in advance, an index which implements the SortedKeyStatisticsAttributeIndex interface, to be added to the collection on the given attribute.

    This object can be accessed first by calling IndexedCollection.getMetadataEngine() to access the MetadataEngine, and then by calling MetadataEngine.getSortedAttributeMetadata(Attribute) for a given attribute.

      • getFrequencyDistribution

        public Stream<KeyFrequency<A>> getFrequencyDistribution()
        Returns the frequencies of distinct keys (a.k.a. attribute values) in the index, in ascending order.

        The KeyFrequency objects encapsulate a key (a.k.a. attribute value), and the frequency (or count) of how many objects in the collection match that key.

      • getKeysAndValues

        public Stream<KeyValue<A,​O>> getKeysAndValues()
        Returns the keys (a.k.a. attribute values) and the objects they match in the index, in ascending order of key.

        Note the same key will be returned multiple times if more than one object has the same key. Also the same object might be returned multiple times, each time for a different key, if the index is built on a multi-value attribute.

        Overrides:
        getKeysAndValues in class AttributeMetadata<A extends Comparable<A>,​O>
        Returns:
        The keys and objects they match in the index, in ascending order of key
